The paper deals with local community detection in large graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and social network analysis. The paper proposes modifications to existing local methods to improve scalability and robustness, which are important issues in computer science. The paper also uses pre-processing techniques and graph diffusions, which are common methods in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
